DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to wrap a data collection within another data object. An `AlbumData` object contains a `DataCollection` of `SongData` objects. The `SongData` collection is wrapped using the `wrap('data')` method when creating the `AlbumData` instance from the `Album` model. This demonstrates wrapping collections within data objects which is supported.
