TITLE: Nullable Properties in Data Object (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates declaring properties as nullable strings within a Laravel Data object. This approach is discouraged in favor of using the `empty()` method for creating blueprints.
SOURCE: https://github.com/spatie/laravel-data/blob/main/docs/as-a-resource/from-data-to-resource.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
class SongData extends Data
{
    public function __construct(
        public ?string $title,
        public ?string $artist,
    ) {
    }

    // ...
}
```
